HEADWORD: bump off
<hw>bump` off"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To kill (a
person); to murder; -- used commonly of planned assassination by
criminals; <as>as, the mob <ex>bumped off</ex> all the
witnesses</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

